note: This CME is a partial halo to the NW in SOHO LASCO C2/C3 and to the NE in STEREO A COR2. The potential source of this CME is visible along the NW limb in SDO/AIA 193 and 171 as moving/opening field lines and an EUV wave.

cmeAnalyses.note: These parameters are based off of the best fit between SOHO LASCO C3 and STEREO A COR2 difference images. Based off of measurements, the longitude could range between 151 degrees and 157 degrees depending on the fit. The latitude may also range between 5 and 15 degrees depending on the fit. Speeds of this CME 600km/s to 760km/s.
